- Wed 24 Apr 2019. Ebola 1st responders threaten strike if security not improved
[Reuters, abridged, edited]
https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-ebola-congo/ebola-first-responders-threaten-strike-if-security-not-improved-idUSKCN1S02L0

At a protest on Wednesday [24 Apr 2019] in Butembo, the biggest city to be affected by the current outbreak, dozens of Congolese doctors and nurses marched behind a banner reading "Ebola exists" and urged authorities to take additional security measures.

"If our security is not guaranteed, we will go on strike from the 1st week of May [2019]," Dr. Kalima Nzanzu said, reading from a memo to Butembo's mayor, Sylvain Kanyamanda.

Kanyamanda told Reuters that he understood the health workers' frustrations and that the government was determined to respond to their demands.

