[4] Vaccine
- Wed 24 Apr 2019. 2nd experimental vaccine
[The Guardian, abridged, edited]
https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2019/apr/24/rumour-violence-congo-drc-ebola-outbreak-out-of-control
[Byline: Esdras Tsongo and Rebecca Ratcliffe]

An experimental vaccine, made by Merck and thought to be highly effective, is being offered to frontline workers as well as known contacts of Ebola patients, and in turn, their contacts. However, health workers warn that there are also delays in reaching contacts. Around one in 10 people offered the vaccine either decline the offer or are absent.

It is likely that a 2nd experimental vaccine, developed by Janssen Pharmaceuticals, could be rolled out within the next 2 months, according to Yap Boum, professor at Mbarara University, Uganda. It's thought the vaccine will be used as a preventative measure in surrounding areas where the disease has not yet spread, but this will require large numbers of health workers to administer the treatment.

"The human resource is really the key point," said Boum, who is also regional representative for Epicenter Africa, the research arm of MSF. "Then you have the logistics: How are you going to deploy it? It seems simple, but when you are in DRC and you see the state of the roads and you are in rainy season, it complicates some of those things.

"The vaccine is not the [magic] bullet," he added. "We may use the 2nd vaccine, but if there is still distrust in the community [the outbreak] will continue."

--
