- Wed 24 Apr 2019. Disease following vaccination
Ministry of Health DRC @MinSanteRDC (https://twitter.com/MinSanteRDC) [edited]

Of more than 90 000 people vaccinated against #Ebola, only 71 developed the disease. Of these, 56 had the 1st symptoms less than 10 days after vaccination, before they could develop their immune protection, and 9 died.

No deaths were recorded among vaccinees who developed #Ebola disease more than 10 days after vaccination. The overall case fatality rate was reduced among all vaccinated persons who developed #Ebola (9 of 71 or 12.6%).

Ir Grace Mugisha @IrGraceMugisha (https://twitter.com/IrGraceMUGISHA)
Replying to @MinSanteRDC
Thank you very much for the work you do and for this digital presence. Just a question, do you know why the vaccinated people developed the disease more than 10 days later?

--
