- Tue 23 Apr 2019. Butembo: REDHO affected by insecurity against Ebola response teams
[Radio Moto Butembo-Beni, online trans., edited]
https://protect2.fireeye.com/url?k=c87a2242-944284ff-c878db77-000babd9fa3f-f1a405538c4c813e&u=http://radiomotofm.info/lirearticle.php?billet=5742

The REDHO / ASBL [non-profit organization] Human Rights Network is concerned about the insecurity of Ebola teams in the town of Butembo. REDHO / ASBL, in its press release of this Mon 22 Apr [2019] made 3 recommendations.

This platform of human rights organizations recommends to the authorities responsible for maintaining order and peace that they prevent damage by protecting the population and its property and paying particular attention to the nursing staff during this period of the epidemic of Ebola virus disease.

[They also recommend to] the attorney general of the Republic of Butembo, as well as the Butembo detached military auditor, that they conduct a sincere investigation to ensure that the perpetrators are tried in accordance with national and international laws.

REDHO also recommends that caregivers remain vigilant in reporting suspected cases to authorized services.

